	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				PvP pretty much sucks. Not the general rule of it. Yes, PvP at it's most fundamental is 'realistic', but there are way too many weenie 13 year old sociopaths waiting to exploit some rule/bug. Happened way too much way back in my UO days, making it about as much fun as pouring boiling cooking oil in ones eyes. You can't emulate 'RL PvP' in an anonymous RP game. Doesn't really work for the aforementioned reason. And others. People already have been exploiting the rules on the current PvP servers(purposely loosing levels) forcing VI to come up with at least a little bit of a fix. And it's oh so much fun to be minding ones business in a newbie zone trying to get at least a couple levels under ones belt only to have a group of(the aforementioned 13 year olds) decide you are their next experience, just as you are about to finish off some lv 1 MoB, barely alive yourself. Then you find out your attackers are all 'Good' races and classes. <BR>
No, this didn't happen to me, but I know it happens. /salute to all those who put up with the crap and manage to make it far on a strictly PvP server. <BR>
But in at least a (more-so) role playing environment, alignment type PvP makes a little more sence. Language barriers are a great idea also. It makes sence, and gives players something to work on. I've got no problem with one character on that server. Most who would play on it will be seasoned players and would know what race/class combo they'd like to play. Eliminating twinking isn't a bad idea also. (or at least making it harder to twink). /ooc /shout and /auction are mostly an annoyance anyway. I turn them off as it is. So limiting and/or loosing them sounds great to me. Nothing like 'listening' to 20 minutes /ooc or /shout conversations in SK (I've got a couple twinks there ;-)<BR>
<BR>
Would I play on the new server? Probably not. Got way too much time and too many friends on my current server. I have started characters on other servers (and yes, a few on the PvP ones when they were adding them), but I personally play for the socail aspect of hanging with some friends. <BR>
<BR>
Whatever happens, enjoy the game or don't play. But don't complain about new server rules. Most of you probably will only try it for a week then return to your current server anyways. Always happens. lol<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
